            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-f09fcd twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-6b4cd0\"><p>Please check the Project Gutenberg Web pages for current donation\nmethods and addresses.  Donations are accepted in a number of other\nways including checks, online payments and credit card donations.\nTo donate, please visit: http://pglaf.org/donate</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000283": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000283",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-f09fcd twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-6b4cd0\"><h4 style=\"\">Section 5.  General Information About Project Gutenberg-tm electronic\nworks.</h4></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000284": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000284",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-f09fcd twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-6b4cd0\"><p>Professor Michael S. Hart is the originator of the Project Gutenberg-tm\nconcept of a library of electronic works that could be freely shared\nwith anyone.  For thirty years, he produced and distributed Project\nGutenberg-tm eBooks with only a loose network of volunteer support.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000285": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000285",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-f09fcd twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-6b4cd0\"><p style=\"\">Project Gutenberg-tm eBooks are often created from several printed\neditions, all of which are confirmed as Public Domain in the U.S.\nunless a copyright notice is included.  Thus, we do not necessarily\nkeep eBooks in compliance with any particular paper edition.</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000286": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000286",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-f09fcd twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-6b4cd0\"><p style=\"\">Most people start at our Web site which has the main PG search facility:</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000287": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000287",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-f09fcd twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-6b4cd0\"><p>     http://www.gutenberg.org<br>\n</p></div>"
        },
        "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000288": {
            "role": "text",
            "title": "$:/plugins/twpub/67e0ec325d809a70/text/000000288",
            "type": "text/vnd.twpub",
            "text": "<div class=\"twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-f09fcd twpub-67e0ec325d809a70-6b4cd0\"><p>This Web site includes information about Project Gutenberg-tm,\nincluding how to make donations to the Project Gutenberg Literary\nArchive Foundation, how to help produce our new eBooks, and how to\nsubscribe to our email newsletter to hear about new eBooks.</p></div>"
        },
